<title>CANADA: Canada Feb bankruptcies rise over year.</title>
<headline>Canada Feb bankruptcies rise over year.</headline>
<dateline>OTTAWA 1997-05-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Bankruptcies in Canada rose to 8,450 in February from 7,947 a year earlier, the Department of Consumer and Corporate Affairs said on Friday.</p>
<p>The department said 1,187 businesses and 7,263 consumers went bankrupt in the month.</p>
<p>In January, 7,865 bankruptcies were recorded.</p>
<p>For the year to date, 16,318 bankruptcies have been registered (2,260 businesses and 14,058 consumers), up from 15,274 in the same period last year.</p>
<p>((Reuters Ottawa Bureau, 613-235-6745))</p>
